reviews.snippet:
鶯谷のラブフォ群を抜けると閑静な住宅街のメイン通りに何と！ウズベキスタン料理店に遭遇？　何故ここに？と思いメニューを見ると昨年行ったサマルカンドのお店と同じ写真🤔🤔　入ってプロフとサムサを頼んだら何とまんまオリジナルの味がリーズナブルな価格で頂けました。
都心にもウズベキスタン料理店はあるけど何かいまいちで日本人用に手を加えてるけど、こちらのお店は具材や油の加減や炊き方、ひよこ豆等正に1年前にサマルカンドやブハラで食べた味そのもので正直驚きました！今度は友人達を連れて再訪します。

extracted_snippet.original:

extracted_snippet.translated:
Going through the Love Photos in Uguisudani, I came across an Uzbek restaurant on the main street of a quiet residential area! Why here? I wondered, and when I looked at the menu, I saw that it had the same picture as the restaurant in Samarkand I visited last year 🤔🤔 I went in and ordered a profio and samsa, and was able to enjoy the exact same original flavor at a reasonable price.
There are Uzbek restaurants in the city, but they're somehow a bit disappointing and are modified to suit Japanese tastes, but the ingredients, amount of oil, cooking method, chickpeas, etc. at this restaurant were exactly the same as the ones I had in Samarkand and Bukhara a year ago, and I was honestly surprised! I'll definitely return with friends next time.

response.snippet:
素敵な口コミをありがとうございます！
本場ウズベキスタンでの味を思い出していただけたこと、大変光栄です。
プロフやサムサの味付け、具材、炊き方など、できる限り現地の味を再現できるよう心がけていますので、そう言っていただけて本当に嬉しいです。
ぜひ次回はご友人の方々と一緒にお越しくださいませ。スタッフ一同、心よりお待ちしております！

Please come again with your friends next time. All the staff look forward to seeing you!

reviews.snippet:
A few years ago, after visiting "Former Iwasaki Residence & Garden", I walked to this restaurant. At that time, though I had no plan to visit Uzbekistan, I had a Uzubekistan edition of "Arukikata (Globe-Trotter Travel Guideook)", a popular travel guide published in Japan.
I enjoyed lunch with Ayran and the delicious honey cake, and had a truly luxurious time. If I recall correctly, their non-alcohol drink had some large portion option, which is hard to find in Japan.
